			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-408050">
									

<p>Truth, Justice, Freedom, Reasonably Priced Love, and a Hard-Boiled Egg.</p>
<p>Y'know, with this SCP, the whole "Procedure 110-Montauk" is definitely the worst bit, but the whole "being tied down and unable to move 24-7" is on the nightmare fuel scale for me as well. I can't say being allowed to move around the rest of the time would make having to undergo the Procedure *fun*, but … That's probably why I thought up the amnesiac thing. If it was me, I'd rather have one horrible happening which I immediately forgot afterwards per day and comparative normalcy the rest of the time (even if "normalcy" is stretching a point when one's still locked up in the Foundation building) than be stuck with nothing to do but await the next horrible happening when I could clearly remember all the ones before it. The amnesiac being used probably doesn't improve the situation all that much, but it did say they have "not given up trying to save SCP-231-7", so they must be trying pretty much everything by now …</p>

							</div>

								
					
